id="post-3854" class="post-3854 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-body-mind category-direct-action tag-ethics tag-oxford-university tag-philosophy tag-work"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2013/06/10/get-help-choosing-an-ethical-career/" title="Permalink to Get Help Choosing an Ethical Career" rel="bookmark">Get Help Choosing an Ethical Career</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2013/06/10 10:57 am"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2013/06/10/get-help-choosing-an-ethical-career/" title="Get Help Choosing an Ethical Career" rel="bookmark">2013/06/10 10:57 am</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p><iframe
width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/JQcfoboTomg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p><a
href="http://80000hours.org/">80,000 Hours</a> is a student run organization at Oxford University that helps people find a job or career in something that makes the world better. This is great for so many obvious reasons &#8211; but the one I love the most is that it shows how philosophy can be applied in your life everyday.</p><p>Do you want to spend 8 (or more) hours a day just earning a couple dollars when you can get paid to make the planet, people, and the world better?</p><blockquote><p>According to the organization’s view of ethics-as-impact, a do-gooder job only “does good” insofar as you are better at it than the person who would have filled the job otherwise. “This is the replaceability factor,” says MacAskill. “The difference between you and the person who would have been in your shoes.” If you’re fully replaceable, you are, quite literally, not making a difference.</p></blockquote><p><a
href="http://www.fastcoexist.com/1682193/how-to-choose-an-ethical-career-with-help-from-oxford-philosophers">Read more at Co.Exist.</a></p><div
