href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2013/05/09/a-sense-of-purpose-is-more-important-than-money-for-workplaces/" title="Permalink to A Sense of Purpose is More Important Than Money for Workplaces" rel="bookmark">A Sense of Purpose is More Important Than Money for Workplaces</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2013/05/09 12:08 pm"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2013/05/09/a-sense-of-purpose-is-more-important-than-money-for-workplaces/" title="A Sense of Purpose is More Important Than Money for Workplaces" rel="bookmark">2013/05/09 12:08 pm</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>In this TED Talk Dan Ariely presents his research into what motivates people to do work and how they feel about their workplace. The findings are interesting because it&#8217;s not necessarily what people do but the reactions to what has been done that provides motivation.</p><p><iframe
